{"source_hash": "25f91db2495688a6", "candidate": {"id": "cand-010", "name": "Kieran Walsh", "raw_cv": "KIERAN WALSH\nkieran.walsh@email.com | London, UK\n\nSENIOR DATA ENGINEER\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nData engineer with 5 years of experience across e-commerce, media, and fintech sectors. Proficient in Python, dbt, and Snowflake. Strong background in data product development and stakeholder management.\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nSenior Data Engineer \u2014 Deliveroo, London (2021\u2013present)\n- Built and maintained dbt models for the rider and restaurant analytics platform\n- Designed Airflow pipelines for daily reporting and product analytics\n- Collaborated with product and finance teams to define key metrics\n- Refactored legacy ETL jobs in Python, reducing runtime by 40%\n\nData Engineer \u2014 The Guardian, London (2019\u20132021)\n- Built audience and content analytics pipelines in BigQuery\n- Worked on subscriber lifetime value modelling data feeds\n\nSKILLS\nPython, SQL, dbt, Snowflake, BigQuery, Airflow, Docker, Git\n\nEDUCATION\nBSc Statistics \u2014 University of Warwick (2016\u20132019)\n\nRIGHT TO WORK\nBritish citizen (Irish dual national)", "raw_linkedin": "Data engineer with five years of experience across some of London's most interesting data-intensive companies \u2014 Deliveroo and The Guardian. I love building data infrastructure that actually gets used and trusted by stakeholders. Strong in dbt, Python, and Snowflake. Interested in my next challenge \u2014 ideally somewhere with interesting data and a healthy work-life balance culture.", "raw_interview_transcript": "Interviewer: Kieran, what draws you to financial data engineering after time in media and e-commerce?\n\nKieran: I'm genuinely attracted to the rigour of financial data. In media you can get away with approximate numbers; in fintech the reconciliation has to be exact. I find that challenge appealing. I've been picking up knowledge on the regulatory side in my own time \u2014 reading about CASS, MiFID data requirements.\n\nInterviewer: Good to hear. What about the five-days-in-office arrangement?\n\nKieran: That's the one thing I'd want to talk through. I'm fully committed to this role and the company, but I've been hoping for a four-day working week. It's been a personal goal for a while \u2014 I coach youth football on Friday evenings and having a compressed schedule would let me manage that much better. Is there any flexibility there, or is five full days genuinely fixed?\n\nInterviewer: It's fixed, unfortunately. The role requires five days at Canary Wharf \u2014 it's a team and culture thing, not just a policy.\n\nKieran: I understand. I'm not going to pretend it's ideal for me. I'd still be very interested in the role \u2014 I'm not going to walk away over it \u2014 but I want to be honest that it's a consideration for me.\n\nInterviewer: We appreciate the honesty. Let's continue the conversation. Salary?\n\nKieran: I'm at \u00a374,000. I'd be looking for \u00a378\u201382,000.", "years_experience": 5.0, "skills": ["Python", "SQL", "dbt", "Snowflake", "BigQuery", "Airflow", "Docker", "Git"], "industries": ["e-commerce", "media", "fintech"], "seniority_level": "senior", "management_experience": false, "education_level": "bachelor", "career_trajectory": "ascending", "interview_score": 0.78, "culture_fit_score": 0.72, "constraints": [{"id": "e2e4baa1", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Current salary \u00a374,000 (confirmed in interview)", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 74000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98}, {"id": "35ef78bc", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Salary expectation minimum \u00a378,000", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 78000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.95}, {"id": "86faff4e", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Salary expectation maximum \u00a382,000", "canonical_key": "salary_max", "value": 82000.0, "operator": "max", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.95}, {"id": "ef56a135", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "work_arrangement", "description": "Prefers four-day working week; currently working five days but would prefer flexibility. Not a dealbreaker but important personal goal.", "canonical_key": "four_day_week", "value": true, "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.88}, {"id": "1addf532", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Currently based in London, UK; comfortable working in London (Canary Wharf mentioned)", "canonical_key": "location_city", "value": "London", "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.92}, {"id": "4b214316", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "work_culture", "description": "Values healthy work-life balance culture; interested in roles with good balance and flexibility", "canonical_key": null, "value": "healthy work-life balance", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.85}, {"id": "70a1b0cd", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "industry_preference", "description": "Attracted to fintech and financial data engineering; values rigour and regulatory knowledge", "canonical_key": "industry_background", "value": "fintech", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.9}]}, "embedding": [-0.04325200617313385, 0.04158225283026695, 0.050173401832580566, -0.013883193023502827, 0.011425693519413471, -0.03848512843251228, 0.0015393041539937258, 0.04694162309169769, -0.00010909365664701909, 0.010510021820664406, -0.022514741867780685, -0.04063965007662773, -0.03296416997909546, -0.013418625108897686, 0.040343403816223145, 0.0517892949283123, -0.026379413902759552, 0.01203165203332901, -0.04381756857037544, -0.011082316748797894, 0.020589139312505722, 0.0004100743099115789, -0.031025098636746407, 0.03328734636306763, 0.030567264184355736, 0.016670605167746544, -